    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA112-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu paruva varaviṉkaṇ āṟṟāḷāya talaiviyait tōḻi vaṟpuṟuttiyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante comforted HER who was unable to bear it during the coming of the season.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA112">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            viruntevaṉ ceykō tōḻi cāra</l>
<l>            larumpaṟa malarnta karuṅkāl vēṅkaic</l>
<l>            curumpimi raṭukkam pulampak kaḷiṟaṭ</l>
<l>            ṭurumpi luḷḷat tarimā vaḻaṅkum</l>
<l>            peruṅka ṉāṭaṉ varavaṟintu virumpi </l>
<l>            mākkaṭaṉ mukantu maṇiniṟat taruvit</l>
<l>            tāḻnīr naṉantalai yaḻuntupaṭap pāay</l>
<l>            malaiyimaip patupōṉ miṉṉic</l>
<l>            cilaiva lēṟṟoṭu ceṟintavim maḻaikkē.</l>
    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>How can I give a feast, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">for this rain, dense with resounding strong strokes [of thunder],</l>
<l rend="indent2">flashing as if [it were] the mountain's twinkling,</l>
<l rend="indent2">spreading lastingly in a vast area water that comes down</l>
<l rend="indent3">from sapphire-coloured waterfalls, drawing from the great sea,</l>
<l rend="indent">while [we] longingly know of the coming of the man</l>
<l rend="indent3">from the land of big stones,</l>
<l rend="indent3">where the lion wanders with unaffected mind,</l>
<l rend="indent3">killing the elephant bull so that the mountain side is lonely,</l>
<l rend="indent4">humming with bees in the black-trunked Vēṅkai trees</l>
<l rend="indent4">come to bloom so that the buds break open on the slope?</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
